# Docker Compose Flask + PostgreSQL Task API

A simple REST API built with **Flask** and **PostgreSQL**, containerized using **Docker** and orchestrated with **Docker Compose**.

This project demonstrates containerization, service communication, persistent storage using Docker volumes, and environment variable configuration.

---

## Features

- Flask REST API
- PostgreSQL database
- Dockerized application
- Docker Compose orchestration
- Persistent storage using Docker Volumes
- Environment variable configuration
- Health endpoint for application monitoring

---

## Project Structure

```
.
├── app.py
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md
```

---

## Architecture

```
                +----------------+
                |    Client      |
                +--------+-------+
                         |
                    HTTP :5001
                         |
                         ▼
                +----------------+
                | Flask API       |
                | Container       |
                +--------+-------+
                         |
                    PostgreSQL
                         |
                         ▼
                +----------------+
                | PostgreSQL      |
                | Container       |
                +--------+-------+
                         |
                         ▼
                Docker Named Volume
                   postgres-data
```

---

## Technologies Used

- Python 3
- Flask
- PostgreSQL 17
- psycopg2
- Docker
- Docker Compose

---

## API Endpoints

### Health Check

```
GET /health
```

Example:

```bash
curl http://localhost:5001/health
```

---

### Get All Tasks

```
GET /tasks
```

Example:

```bash
curl http://localhost:5001/tasks
```

---

### Create Task

```
POST /tasks
```

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"title":"Learn Docker"}' \
http://localhost:5001/tasks
```

---

## Running the Project

### Clone Repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd 02-docker-compose
```

### Start Application

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

The application will be available at:

```
http://localhost:5001
```

---

## Verify the Application

Health Check

```bash
curl http://localhost:5001/health
```

Get Tasks

```bash
curl http://localhost:5001/tasks
```

Create Task

```bash
curl -X POST \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"title":"Learn Docker Compose"}' \
http://localhost:5001/tasks
```

---

## Persistent Storage

PostgreSQL data is stored using a Docker named volume.

Stopping containers:

```bash
docker compose down
```

does **not** delete the database.

Removing the volume:

```bash
docker compose down -v
```

will permanently delete all stored data.

